20rearm%20for%20future%20aggression%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20will%20need%20to%20keep%20up%20sanctions%20against%20Moscow%20through%20this%20decade%2C%20in%20order%20to%20cut%20Russia's%20energy%20revenues%20by%20half%2C%20a%20US%20diplomat%20told%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F277c1f9c-3f0f-4562-b0f0-80b390012087%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20something%20that%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20stick%20to%20for%20years%20to%20come%2C%20as%20long%20as%20%5BPresident%20Vladimir%5D%20Putin%20persists%20in%20this%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Geoffrey%20Pyatt%20said%2C%20the%20US%20assistant%20secretary%20of%20state%20for%20energy%20resources.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERestricting%20Moscow's%20oil%20and%20gas%20revenues%20through%20the%20long%20term%20will%20ensure%20that%20Russia%20cannot%20promptly%20rearm%20itself%20for%20any%20future%20military%20operations%2C%20he%20added%2C%20in%20the%20case%20that%20peace%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20achieved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWestern%20sanctions%20were%20first%20applied%20in%20February%202022%2C%20after%20Russian%20forces%20invaded%20Ukraine%20that%20same%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20have%20since%20included%20a%20%2460%20dollar%20price%20cap%20on%20oil%20exports%2C%20and%20curbs%20on%20the%20trade%20of%20Russian%20oil%20products%20and%20diesel.%20In%20retaliation%2C%20Moscow%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fcommodities%2Frussia-oil-gas-energy-revenue-western-sanctions-ukraine-war-economy-2023-6%5C%22%3Ecut%20off%20gas%20flows%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Europe%2C%20also%20adding%20to%20a%20drop%20in%20energy%20revenues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20in%20November%2C%20the%20US%20applied%20the%20first%20sanctions%20on%20Russia's%20gas%20export%2C%20targeting%20a%20liquefied%20natural%20gas%20development%20known%20as%20Arctic%20LNG%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%