ressional-term-limits-experts-weigh-pros-and-cons%2Farticleshow%2F105663768.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105663768.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EA%20recent%20Pew%20Research%20Center%20survey%20reveals%20that%2087%25%20of%20Americans%20support%20term%20limits%20for%20members%20of%20Congress.%20Gov.%20Ron%20DeSantis%2C%20a%20potential%20presidential%20candidate%2C%20endorses%20the%20idea%2C%20highlighting%20its%20bipartisan%20appeal.%20The%20U.S.%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20in%201995%20that%20implementing%20term%20limits%20would%20require%20a%20constitutional%20amendment.%20Constitutional%20law%20professor%20Louis%20Virelli%20suggests%20an%20alternative%20route%20through%20Article%20Five%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20U.S.%20Term%20Limits%20reports%20that%20six%20states%2C%20including%20Florida%2C%20have%20submitted%20applications%20to%20advocate%20for%20term%20limits.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Famericans-rally-for-congressional-term-limits-experts-weigh-pros-and-cons%2Farticleshow%2F105663768.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Famericans-rally-for-congressional-term-limits-experts-weigh-pros-and-cons%2Famp_articleshow%2F105663768.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Famericans-rally-for-congressional-term-limits-experts-weigh-pros-and-cons%2Famp_articleshow%2F105663768.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BWith%20Advent%20Of%20Troll%20Armies...%26quot%3B%3A%20Chief%20Justice%20On%20Free%20Speech%20On%20Internet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20on%20Friday%20raised%20concerns%20over%20overwhelming%20barrage%20of%20speech%20that%20distorts%20the%20truth%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20troll%20armies%20and%20organised%20disinformation%20campaigns%20across%20social%20media%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTraditionally%2C%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20was%20deemed%20to%20be%20an%20essential%20part%20of%20civil%20rights%20activism%20because%20of%20the%20fear%20that%20the%20government%20would%20prevent%20certain%20kinds%20of%20speech%20from%20entering%20the%20marketplace%2C%26quot%3B%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%20at%20the%2014th%20Justice%20VM%20Tarkunde%20memorial%20lecture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20advent%20of%20troll%20armies%20and%20organised%20disinformation%20campaigns%20across%20different%20social%20media%20platforms%2C%20the%20fear%20is%20that%20there%20is%20an%20overwhelming%20barrage%20of%20speech%20that%20distorts%20the%20truth%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20epistemological%20battle%20of%20sorts%20was%20explained%20eloquently%20in%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20in%202020%2C%20where%20it%20said%20'the%20spewing%20of%20falsehoods%20isn't%20meant%20to%20win%20any%20battle%20of%20ideas.%20Its%20goal%20is%20to%20prevent%20the%20actual%20battle%20from%20being%20fought'.%20Therefore%2C%20we%20cannot%20fall%20back%20on%20traditional%20notions%20of%20free%20speech%20and%20must%20find%20new%20theoretical%20frameworks%20to%20locate%20free%20speech%20on%20the%20internet%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said%20the%20intricate%20interplay%20between%20surveillance%20by%20the%20state%20and%20an%20individual's%20right%20to%20privacy%20has%20been%20a%20subject%20of%20compelling%20debate%20within%20Indian%20jurisprudence.%20The%20first%20case%20that%20dealt%20with%20privacy%20was%20R%20Rajagopal%20vs%20State%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20the%20court%20determined%20that%20a%20magazine%20has%20the%20right%20to%20publish%20an%20autobiography%20penned%20by%20a%20prisoner%2C%20even%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20prisoner's%20consent%20or%20authorisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDespite%20efforts%20by%20prison%20officials%20to%20hinder%20the%20publication%20by%20compelling%20the%20prisoner%20to%20request%20its%20non-publication%2C%20the%20court%20underscored%20the%20need%20to%20maintain%20a%20delicate%20equilibrium%20between%20press%20freedom%20and%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%2C%26quot%3B%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Justice%20Tarkunde%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said%20the%20core%20emphasis%20of%20the%20civil%20liberties%20movement%20that%20Justice%20Tarkunde%20championed%20is%20mirrored%20by%20digital%20rights%20activism%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%2C%20looking%20back%20on%20Justice%20Tarkunde's%20dedication%20to%20civil%20liberties%2C%20said%20he%20inspired%20him%20as%20a%20young%20lawyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B...It%20continues%20to%20inspire%20me%20as%20I%20serve%20as%20a%20judge%20of%20a%20constitutional%20court.%20That%20Justice%20Tarkunde%20is%20regarded%20as%20the%20'Father%20of%20the%20Civil%20Rights%20Movement'%20is%20no%20surprise.%20In%20every%20role%20he%20donned%20-%20as%20a%20senior%20advocate%2C%20High%20Court%20judge%2C%20and%20activist%20-%20he%20was%20steadfast%20in%20his%20commitment%20to%20democracy%2C%20radical%20humanism%2C%20and%20civil%20liberty%2C%26quot%3B%20Chief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B...%20No%20book%2C%20academic%20article%20or%20chronicle%20of%20the%20internal%20emergency%20imposed%20in%20the%201970s%20is%20complete%20without%20a%20reference%20to%20Justice%20Tarkunde's%20spirited%20defence%20of%20personal%20liberty%20and%20democracy%2C%20both%20inside%20and%20outside%20the%20courtroom%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701450120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fnvkb7j88_chief-justice-dy-chandrachud_625x300_01_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsubject-of-compelling-debate-says-chief-justice-dy-chandrachud-on-surveillance-vs-right-to-privacy-4625713%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%20on%20Friday%20raised%20concerns%20over%20overwhelming%20barrage%20of%20speech%20that%20distorts%20the%20truth%20with%20the%20advent%20of%20troll%20armies%20and%20organised%20disinformation%20campaigns%20across%20social%20media%20platforms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsubject-of-compelling-debate-says-chief-justice-dy-chandrachud-on-surveillance-vs-right-to-privacy-4625713%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsubject-of-compelling-debate-says-chief-justice-dy-chandrachud-on-surveillance-vs-right-to-privacy-4625713%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fsubject-of-compelling-debate-says-chief-justice-dy-chandrachud-on-surveillance-vs-right-to-privacy-4625713%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Says%20%E2%80%98No%20Question%E2%80%99%20of%20TN%20Governor%20Referring%2010%20Bills%20to%20President%20After%20Withholding%20Assent%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F26113713%2FScreenshot-2022-04-26-at-11.37.07-AM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%20said%20a%20governor%20cannot%20refer%20to%20the%20president%20Bills%20that%20they%20have%20previously%20withheld%20assent%20to%2C%20advising%C2%A0Tamil%20Nadu%20governor%20R.N.%20Ravi%20to%20resolve%20the%20impasse%20with%20the%20state%20government%20over%2010%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheprint.in%2Fjudiciary%2Fcant-withhold-assent-then-refer-to-president-sc-asks-tn-governor-to-resolve-impasse-over-bills%2F1867039%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Print%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20made%20the%20verbal%20suggestion%20to%20attorney%20general%20R.%20Venkataramani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavi%20had%20withheld%20assent%20to%2010%20Bills%2C%20that%20pertained%20to%20modifications%20in%20state%20university%20laws%2C%20which%20the%20legislature%20passed%20again%20without%20any%20amendments%20but%20later%20referred%20them%20to%20the%20President%2C%20just%20days%20after%20the%20top%20court%20questioned%20the%20governor%20for%20sitting%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2013%2C%20the%20governor%20said%20he%20had%20withheld%20his%20assent%20to%20the%2010%20Bills%2C%20which%20also%20took%20away%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20powers%2C%20as%20chancellor%20of%20state%20universities%2C%20to%20appoint%20vice-chancellors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESubsequently%2C%20the%20state%20assembly%20convened%20a%20special%20session%20on%20November%2018%20and%20passed%20them%20again.%20On%20November%2020%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20asked%20the%20governor%20about%20the%20pending%20Bills.%20On%20November%2028%2C%20the%20governor%20referred%20them%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Print%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20under%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20governor%20has%20only%20three%20options%20%E2%80%94%20grant%20assent%2C%20withhold%20assent%20or%20refer%20it%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20%E2%80%9Calternatives%E2%80%9D%20and%20once%20he%20has%20withheld%20assent%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20is%20no%20question%20of%20him%20referring%20them%20to%20the%20president%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20CJI%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20stressed%20once%20again%20that%20the%20proviso%20of%20Article%20200%20does%20not%20allow%20the%20governor%20to%20stall%20a%20Bill%20once%20it%20is%20re-enacted%20by%20the%20assembly.%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20referred%20to%20the%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20on%20November%2010%20concerning%20the%20Punjab%20governor%E2%80%99s%20delay%C2%A0in%20assenting%20to%20certain%20Bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fsc-says-no-question-of-tamil-nadu-governor-referring-10-re-enacted-bills-to-president-now%2Farticle67593997.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu%20government%20told%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%20that%20Ravi%20was%20exhibiting%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20obstinacy%E2%80%9D%20by%20referring%20the%2010%20re-enacted%20Bills%20to%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAG%C2%A0Venkataramani%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20argued%20that%20the%20governor%20had%20%E2%80%9Csimply%20withheld%20assent%E2%80%9D%20on%20November%2013%20and%20did%20not%20send%20them%20back.%20%E2%80%9CNow%2C%20this%20was%20not%20a%20case%20when%20the%20Governor%20had%20asked%20the%20Assembly%20to%20reconsider%20the%20Bills%20or%20had%20recommended%20changes.%20Here%2C%20he%20had%20only%20communicated%20to%20the%20Assembly%20on%20November%2013%20that%20he%20had%20withheld%20assent%E2%80%A6%20The%20Bills%20were%20not%20technically%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20Assembly%20for%20reconsideration%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20argued%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSo%2C%20you%20are%20saying%20the%20governor%20can%20just%20withhold%20consent%20and%20virtually%20kill%20the%20Bills%3F%E2%80%9D%20the%20CJI%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20also%20asked%20the%20governor%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20chief%20minister.%20%E2%80%9CLet%20them%20sit%20down%20and%20discuss%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20AG%E2%80%99s%20response%20was%20%E2%80%9Cbleak%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20that%20there%20were%20cases%20when%20%E2%80%9Cboth%20do%20not%20have%20any%20bonhomie%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701450022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F04%2F26113713%2FScreenshot-2022-04-26-at-11.37.07-AM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-tn-governor-10-bills-impasse%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22CJI%20Chandrachud%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20under%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20governor%20has%20only%20three%20'alternatives'%20%E2%80%94%20grant%20assent%2C%20withhold%20assent%20or%20refer%20it%20to%20the%20president.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-tn-governor-10-bills-impasse%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tamil%20Nadu%3A%20Police%20Arrest%20ED%20Official%20Who%20Was%20Caught%20'Red-Handed'%20While%20Allegedly%20Accepting%20Bribe%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F07104156%2Fprison-bars-jail-imprisoned-justice-arrest.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Police%20has%20arrested%20an%20officer%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20Ankit%20Tiwari%20and%20said%20he%20had%20been%20caught%20%E2%80%9Cred-handed%E2%80%9D%20while%20accepting%20a%20bribe%20of%20Rs%2020%20lakh%20from%20a%20doctor%20in%20Dindigul%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FANI%2Fstatus%2F1730607708351652064%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Equoted%20by%20news%20agencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20saying%20that%20he%20along%20with%20his%20team%20of%20ED%20officers%20had%20been%20threatening%20several%20people%20and%20receiving%20bribes%20in%20the%20name%20of%20closing%20their%20case%20at%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate.%20DVAC%20(Directorate%20of%20Vigilance%20and%20Anti-Corruption)%20officials%20caught%20him%20with%20Rs%2020%20lakh%20cash%20in%20Dindigul.%20The%20investigation%20is%20underway.%20DVAC%20also%20searched%20the%20ED%20Office%20in%20Madurai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETiwari%20and%20his%20team%20intimidated%20and%20received%20bribes%20from%20several%20persons%20in%C2%A0exchange%C2%A0of%20dropping%20charges%20against%20them%2C%20the%20police%20alleged%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Ftamil-nadu%2Falleged-ed-official-arrested-in-tamil-nadu-for-taking-bribes-to-close-cases%5C%22%3Eas%20per%20%3Cem%3EThe%20News%20Minute%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%20This%20alleged%20bribery%20racket%20was%20discovered%20months%20after%20ED%20raids%20on%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20leaders%20and%20their%20associates.%20Former%20minister%20for%20Electricity%2C%20Prohibition%2C%20and%20Excise%20V.%20Senthil%20Balaji%20was%20arrested%20earlier%20this%20year%20by%20ED%20for%20his%20cash-for-jobs%20scam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%3Cem%3E%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reports%20that%20Tiwari%20is%20a%202016-batch%20officer%2C%20who%20had%20previously%20served%20in%20Gujarat%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Ftamil-nadu-police-arrest-senior-ed-officer-for-accepting-bribe-of-rs-20-lakh-9050047%2F%5C%22%3Eis%20currently%20posted%20in%20Madurai.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20Higher%20Education%20Minister%20K%20Ponmudi%E2%80%99s%20home%20in%20Villupuram%20was%20also%20raided%20by%20ED.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20November%20this%20year%2C%20Rajasthan%E2%80%99s%20Anti-Corruption%20Bureau%20(ACB)%20arrested%20two%20ED%20officials%20on%20bribery%20charges%2C%20a%20day%20after%20the%20agency%20issued%20summons%20to%20the%20sons%20of%20the%20state%20Congress%20Committee%20Chief%20Govind%20Singh%20Dotasra.%20Dotasra%E2%80%99s%20sons%2C%20Abhilash%20and%20Avinash%2C%20had%20been%20summoned%20by%20the%20ED%20with%20reference%20to%20an%20alleged%20exam%20paper%20leak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20DMK-led%20state%20government%20had%20moved%20the%20Madras%20high%20court%20against%20ED%20summons%20to%2010%20district%20collectors%20as%20part%20of%20an%20investigation%20into%20alleged%20irregularities%20and%20malpractices%20in%20the%20mining%20and%20sale%20of%20river%20sand%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20The%20high%20court%20had%20stayed%20the%20summons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20the%20controversy%20regarding%20action%20by%20state%20police%20on%20central%20agency%20officers%20goes%2C%20there%20is%20a%20view%20that%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Vigilance%20and%20Anti-Corruption%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20is%20%E2%80%9Cwell%20within%20its%20jurisdiction%20to%20arrest%20an%20ED%20officer%20(Central%20Govt%20employee)%20on%20bribery%20allegations.%20With%20the%20State%20Govt%20revoking%20General%20Consent%20to%20CBI%20under%20Sec%206%20of%20DSPE%20Act%2C%20State%20Police%20has%20sole%20jurisdiction%20over%20Central%20Govt%20employees%20too%20in%20its%20territory%20under%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKerala%20high%20court%20in%20a%20judgement%20this%20year%20ruled%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20special%20provision%20in%20the%20P.C%20Act%20or%20DSPE%20Act%20excluding%20or%20preventing%20the%20State%20police%20or%20a%20Special%20Agency%20of%20the%20State%20from%20investigating%20cases%20relating%20to%20the%20corruption%20of%20the%20Central%20Government%20employees.%20None%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20P.C%20Act%20or%20DSPE%20Act%20authorises%20CBI%20or%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20or%20any%20other%20Central%20Government%20Agency%20alone%20to%20investigate%20in%20matters%20relating%20to%20the%20Central%20Government%20employees%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EKerala%20HC%20in%20a%202023%20judgment%20has%20held%20as%20follows%3A%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20special%20provision%20in%20the%20P.C%20Act%20or%20DSPE%20Act%20excluding%20or%20preventing%20the%20State%20police%20or%20a%20Special%20Agency%20of%20the%20State%20from%20investigating%20cases%20relating%20to%20the%20corruption%20of%20the%20Central%20Government%20employees.%20None%20of%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FyoV41Nr7VC%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FyoV41Nr7VC%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Arvind%20Gunasekar%20(%40arvindgunasekar)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Farvindgunasekar%2Fstatus%2F1730616292867027244%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%201%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20no%20response%20from%20ED%20officials%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Ftamil-nadu-police-arrest-ed-officer-for-accepting-bribe-of-20-lakh-101701434295595.html%5C%22%3Ereports%3Cem%3E%20Hindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701449753000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F07104156%2Fprison-bars-jail-imprisoned-justice-arrest.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftamil-nadu-police-arrest-ed-official-who-was-caught-red-handed-while-allegedly-accepting-bribe%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20that%20an%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20official%20has%20been%20arrested%20on%20bribery%20charges.%20Last%20month%2C%20Rajasthan%E2%80%99s%20Anti-Corruption%20Bureau%20arrested%20two%20ED%20officials%20on%20bribery%20charges%2C%20a%20day%20after%20the%20agency%20issued%20summons%20to%20the%20sons%20of%20the%20state%20Congress%20Committee%20Chief.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftamil-nadu-police-arrest-ed-official-who-was-caught-red-handed-while-allegedly-accepting-bribe%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Centre%20says%20over%20120%2C000%20new%20companies%20incorpo