ncerned%2C%20groups%20which%20organise%20protests%20against%20them%20on%20campus%2C%20and%20a%20pliant%20media%20which%20engages%20in%20defamation%20of%20the%20academics%20as%20terror%20supporters%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20urges%20the%20Indian%20government%20and%20political%20parties%20to%20cease%20criminalizing%20solidarity%20protests%20with%20Palestine%2C%20citing%20examples%20of%20FIRs%20against%20students%20and%20detentions%20in%20various%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20opposition%20parties%20have%20failed%20to%20show%20sufficient%20solidarity%20with%20the%20people%20of%20Palestine%20and%20have%20thus%20betrayed%20the%20history%20of%3Cbr%3E%5CnIndia%E2%80%99s%20own%20freedom%20struggle%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20further%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20calls%20on%20university%20administrations%20to%20uphold%20their%20statutory%20and%20constitutional%20obligations%2C%20respecting%20the%20rights%20of%20faculty%20and%20students%20to%20organize%20talks%20and%20invite%20speakers%20without%20interference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20full%20statement%2C%20with%20the%20names%20of%20the%20signatories%2C%20is%20reproduced%20below.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStatement%20of%20Solidarity%20with%20Palestine%20and%20Condemnation%20of%20Attacks%20on%20Academic%20Freedom%20Related%20to%20Palestine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20academics%20and%20other%20concerned%20persons%2C%20we%2C%20the%20undersigned%2C%20are%20outraged%20at%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20discussions%20on%20the%20ongoing%20war%20against%20Palestine%20are%20being%20silenced%20on%20Indian%20campuses%2C%20and%20in%20the%20public%20sphere%20more%20broadly.%20We%20are%20issuing%20this%20statement%20to%20call%20upon%20university%20administrators%20and%20the%20government%20to%20respect%20our%20academic%20freedom.%20We%20would%20also%20like%20to%20remind%20everyone%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20long%20history%20of%20