ttps%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01172550%2Fimage-1566.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20November%2C%20at%20the%20Jehangir%20Art%20Gallery%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20that%20actor%2C%20director%2C%20and%20painter%2C%20Amol%20Palekar%20opened%20his%20solo%20show%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Through%20the%20Radiance%E2%80%99.%20Curated%20by%20film%20director%20and%20Palekar%E2%80%99s%20wife%2C%20Sandhya%20Gokhale%2C%20it%20is%20a%20series%20of%20abstract%20works%20interspersed%20with%20traditional%20Rajasthani%20%3Cem%3Ekavad%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20storytelling%20tool%20with%20panels%20that%20aid%20a%20narrative.%20The%20lighting%20is%20focused%20and%20cinematic%2C%20and%20the%20canvases%20are%20framed%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20adds%20depth%20to%20the%20paintings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalekar%2C%20who%20graduated%20from%20the%20JJ%20School%20of%20Arts%2C%20started%20out%20as%20a%20painter%20with%20his%20first%20solo%20show%20in%201967.%20It%20was%20in%20the%20same%20year%20that%20he%20took%20his%20first%20steps%20in%20theatre%20through%20%3Cem%3EChup!%20Court%20Chalu%20Hai%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20in%20film%20with%20Govind%20Nihalani%20and%20Satyadev%20Dubey%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EShantata!%20Court%20Chalu%20Aahe%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20two%20back%20to%20back%20hits%20in%20Hindi%20films%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3ERajnigandha%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1974)%20and%20%3Cem%3EChhoti%20Si%20Baat%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1976)%2C%20Palekar%2C%20a%20well-known%20name%20of%20the%20Mumbai%20stage%2C%20became%20a%20nationally%20known%20name%2C%20playing%20an%20Everyman%20character%20whom%20the%20middle%20classes%20could%20identify%20with.%20Paintings%20took%20a%20backseat%20and%20Palekar%E2%80%99s%20life%20was%20made%20of%20the%20stage%20and%20film%20sets.%20He%20played%20memorable%20roles%20and%20was%20a%20regular%20in%20Basu%20Chatterjee%E2%80%99s%20and%20Hrishikesh%20Mukherjee%E2%80%99s%20films.%20Palekar%20terms%20this%20period%20in%20his%20life%20as%20his%20first%20innings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20on%20to%20his%20second%2C%20since%202014%2C%20Palekar%20is%20back%20to%20painting%20with%20renewed%20vigour%20and%20armed%20with%20his%20learnings%20from%20the%20performing%20arts.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20basic%20difference%20between%20the%20performing%20arts%2Fcinema%2C%20and%20visual%20arts%20is%20that%20in%20the%20former%2C%20you%20are%20trying%20to%20communicate%20with%20another%20person%2C%20and%20presenting%20your%20art.%20With%20visual%20arts%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20an%20inward%20journey.%20It%E2%80%99s%20diametrically%20opposite%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20wisdom%20in%20performing%20arts%20and%20cinema%20gave%20me%20quite%20a%20few%20insights%20for%20this%20inward%20journey.%20It%20has%20made%20me%20richer%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20he%20tells%20us%2C%20is%20especially%20true%2C%20of%20his%20last%20exhibition%2C%20where%20he%20has%20become%20more%20confident%20and%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20find%20the%20need%20to%20say%20too%20much.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20theatre%2C%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20hold%20a%20pause.%20In%20between%20two%20lines%2C%20the%20pause%20that%20I%20hold%20is%20completely%20my%20victory%20as%20an%20actor.%20Not%20saying%20anything%20and%20yet%20being%20expressive%20is%20something%20I%20brought%20back%20to%20my%20second%20innings%20in%20visual%20arts.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20fill%20up%20the%20entire%20canvas.%20I%20am%20not%20scared%20of%20having%20said%20just%20a%20little.%20I%20have%20realised%20that%20the%20unspoken%20that%20you%20convey%20through%20a%20pause%20or%20texture%2C%20is%20powerful%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01170013%2Fimage-1561.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221131%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01170013%2Fimage-1561.png%201131w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01170013%2Fimage-1561-300x198.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01170013%2Fimage-1561-1024x676.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687286%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22747%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98I%20don%E2%80%99t%20fill%20up%20the%20entire%20canvas.%20I%20am%20not%20scared%20of%20having%20said%20just%20a%20little%2C%E2%80%99%20says%20Amol%20Palekar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalekar%20uses%20the%20medium%20of%20oil%20paints%20that%20is%20both%20rigid%20and%20difficult%20to%20work%20with.%20He%20finds%20acrylic%20too%20synthetic%2C%20Gokhale%20steps%20in%20to%20say.%20His%20current%20work%20is%20not%20just%20visually%20different%20but%20technically%20accomplished%2C%20too.%20His%20brush%20strokes%20are%20stronger%20and%20more%20confident%2C%20and%20the%20use%20of%20colour%20is%20exuberant%2C%20without%20giving%20in%20to%20the%20loud.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPainted%20during%20the%20pandemic%20that%20the%20duo%20chose%20to%20spend%20in%20their%20Pune%20home%2C%20these%20works%2C%20Palekar%20tells%20us%2C%20were%20an%20attempt%20to%20find%20the%20ray%20of%20light%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20tunnel.%20His%20use%20of%20black%20canvases%20and%20hues%20like%20red%2C%20orange%2C%20green%2C%20and%20cobalt%20blue%2C%20speak%20of%20this%20duality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20reflective%20of%20how%20I%20dealt%20with%20the%20pandemic.%20If%20we%20think%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20was%20completely%20dark%20and%20full%20of%20depression%20and%20pessimism.%20It%20was%20like%20being%20in%20a%20gigantic%20tunnel%2C%20you%20see%20nothing%2C%20and%20you%20feel%20nothing.%20You%20have%20no%20clue%20when%20or%20if%20this%20will%20end.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20chose%20black%20canvas%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20there%20is%20always%20light%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20tunnel.%20This%20is%20how%20I%20started%20facing%20the%20black%20canvas%20and%20trying%20to%20find%20the%20light%20that%20will%20give%20us%20hope%2C%20relief%2C%20and%20exuberance.%20The%20canvas%20started%20talking%20to%20me%2C%20through%20bright%20colours%20and%20bold%20strokes.%20I%20started%20exploring%20that%20feeling%20of%20joy%20and%20celebration%20that%20one%20needs%20to%20have%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkin%20to%20an%20earlier%20series%20of%20paintings%20titled%20%E2%80%98Trickles%E2%80%99%2C%20Palekar%E2%80%99s%20mastery%20of%20oil%20paint%20has%20enabled%20him%20to%20infuse%20in%20it%20a%20watercolour-like%20ability.%20The%20trickles%20of%20paint%2C%20streaming%20down%20are%20nearly%20translucent.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20this%20focus%20on%20texture%2C%20technique%2C%20and%20brush%20strokes%20that%20makes%20this%20series%20different%20from%20others%2C%E2%80%9D%20Gokhale%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01171810%2Fimage-1564.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22757%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01171810%2Fimage-1564.png%20757w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01171810%2Fimage-1564-300x298.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01171810%2Fimage-1564-150x150.png%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-687293%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22752%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20picture%20from%20Amol%20Palekar%E2%80%99s%20exhibition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalekar%E2%80%99s%20abstra