0to%20become%20a%20war%20hero.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAction%20In%20Burma%2C%201942%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES.H.F.J%20Manekshaw%20was%20posted%20in%20the%204th%20Battalion%20of%20the%2012th%20Frontier%20Force%20as%20a%20Captain%20in%20Burma%20and%20witnessed%20action%20during%20World%20War%20II%20when%20the%20Japanese%20were%20at%20the%20eastern%20doorstep%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Americans%20wanted%20to%20keep%20the%20Japanese%20busy%20in%20China%2C%20while%20the%20Japanese%20Imperial%20Army%2C%20apart%20from%20Burma's%20resources%2C%20wanted%20to%20use%20it%20to%20cut%20off%20American%20military%20supply%20lines%20to%20already%20isolated%20China%20and%20use%20Burma%20as%20a%20launching%20pad%20for%20operations%20in%20British%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESam%20Manekshaw's%204%2F12%20FF%20under%20the%2017th%20Indian%20Infantry%20Division%20was%20deployed%20in%20the%20defense%20of%20Burma%20in%201942.%20The%20stretched%20British%20forces%20retreated%20to%20the%20Sittang%20railway%20bridge%20after%20the%20Japanese%20entered%20Burma%20and%20reached%20the%20Bilin%20River%20almost%2048%20km%20south%20of%20Sittang.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plan%20was%20to%20cross%20the%20Sittang%20River%2C%20which%20runs%20north%20to%20south%2C%20and%20a%20small%20bridgehead%20was%20defended%20by%20undermanned%203%20Burma%20Rifles.%20Sam%20Manekshaw's%204%2F12%20FF%20was%20sent%20to%20reinforce%20the%20troops%20on%20the%20east%20of%20the%20bridgehead.%20The%20troops%20had%20to%20cross%20the%20river%20east%20to%20west%20on%20February%2022%20and%20then%20demolish%20the%20bridge%20with%20explosives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAttack%20and%20Counter%20Attack%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESam%20Manekshaw%20was%20commanding%20the%20'A'%20company%20of%204%2F12%20FF.%20The%20soldiers%20from%20the%20Japanese%201%2F215%20Regiment%20emerged%20from%20the%20jungles%20and%20attacked%20the%20Sittang%20village%20to%20take%20over%20the%20bridge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20Battle%20of%20Sittang%20Bridge%20%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22An%20illustration%20of%20Battle%20of%20Sittang%20Bridge%20%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fm2dr2vu8_sittang-bridge-_625x300_01_December_23.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20Battle%20of%20Sittang%20Bridge%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cspan%3EPhoto%20Credit%3A%20Image%20posted%20on%20Facebook%20by%20Gurkha%20Museum%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Japanese%20had%20taken%20control%20of%20the%20Buddha%20and%20Pagoda%20hill%20to%20dominate%20the%20approach.%20Captain%20Sam%20Maneskshaw's%20'A'%20company%20along%20with%20Duke%20Of%20Wellington's%202nd%20Company%20counterattacked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECaptain%20Manekshaw%20was%20tasked%20to%20defend%20the%20approach%20from%20the%20left%20of%20the%20Sittang%20bridge.%20The%20counterattack%20was%20successful%2C%20but%20he%20suffered%20nine%20bullet%20injuries%20in%20his%20abdomen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%2C%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20recalls%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20chap%20(Japanese%20soldier)%20emerged%20from%20the%20bushes%20and%20opened%20a%20burst%20of%20fire%20with%20his%20Tommy%20gun.%20I%20received%20nine%20bullets%20in%20my%20abdomen%2C%20and%20no%20one%20thought%20I%20would%20ever%20live.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMajor%20General%20David%20Cowan%2C%20the%20GOC-in-C%20of%20the%2017th%20Infantry%20Indian%20Division%2C%20saw%20Captain%20Manekhsaw%20and%20pinned%20his%20Military%20Cross%20on%20the%20injured%20Manekshaw's%20uniform%20to%20honour%20him%20as%20the%20gallantry%20medal%20was%20not%20awarded%20posthumously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Manekshaw%20was%20awarded%20the%20Military%20Cross.%20Clipping%20of%20London%20Gazette%2C%201941%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Sam%20Manekshaw%20was%20awarded%20the%20Military%20Cross.%20Clipping%20of%20London%20Gazette%2C%201941%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F1ejftde_london-gazette-1941_625x300_01_December_23.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESam%20Manekshaw%20was%20awarded%20the%20Military%20Cross.%20Clipping%20of%20London%20Gazette%2C%201942%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHumor%20In%20The%20Face%20Of%20Death%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECaptain%20Sam's%20batman%20(a%20soldier%20assisting%20an%20officer)%2C%20Sher%20Singh%2C%20carried%20him%20on%20his%20shoulder%20to%20the%20surgeon.%20The%20Australian%20doctor%20refused%20to%20treat%20him%20due%20to%20his%20serious%20abdomen%20injuries%20and%20his%20grim%20chances%20of%20survival%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BCan't%20waste%20my%20time%20over%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20regained%20consciousness%2C%20the%20surgeon%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20happened%20to%20you%2C%20young%20chap%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20injured%20Manekshaw%20responded%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20bloody%20mule%20kicked%20me.%26quot%3B%20The%20surgeon%20laughed%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BOh!%20You%20have%20a%20sense%20of%20humour.%20You're%20worth%20saving.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESam%20Bahadur%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%2010%20Gorkha%20Regiments%20in%20the%20British%20Indian%20Army%2C%20and%20only%20British%20officers%20were%20allowed%20to%20command%20the%20battalions.%20When%20the%20British%20left%20in%201947%2C%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20became%20the%20first%20Indian%20to%20command%20a%20Gorkha%20Battalion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESam%20Manekshaw%20commanded%20the%208th%20Gorkha%20Rifles.%20He%20met%20a%20Gorkha%20sentry%20and%20asked%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20your%20name%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20he%20said%2C%20Harka%20Bahadur%20Gurung.%20Sam%20Manekshaw%20asked%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20know%20my%20name%3F%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20sentry%20paused%20for%20a%20second%20and%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BSam%20Bahadur%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701430980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2017-09%2Fsam-manekshaw_650x400_61505715222.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbattle-of-sittang-bridge-when-sam-manekshaw-braved-death-in-1942-sam-bahadur-battle-of-burma-world-war-ii-4624376%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20life%20of%20Field%20Marshal%20Sam%20Hormusji%20Framji%20Jamshedji%20Manekshaw%20has%20been%20turned%20into%20a%20motion%20picture%2C%20'Sam%20Bahadur%2C'%20which%20was%20released%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbattle-of-sittang-bridge-when-sam-manekshaw-braved-death-in-1942-sam-bahadur-battle-of-burma-world-war-ii-4624376%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbattle-of-sittang-bridge-when-sam-manekshaw-braved-death-in-1942-sam-bahadur-battle-of-burma-world-war-ii-4624376%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbattle-of-sittang-bridge-when-sam-manekshaw-braved-death-in-1942-sam-bahadur-battle-of-burma-world-war-ii-4624376%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Argentina%20won't%20join%20Brics%20as%20scheduled%2C%20says%20member%20of%20Javier%20Milei's%20transition%20team%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701430731000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105658048%2Cimgsize-777457.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fargentina-wont-join-brics-as-scheduled-says-member-of-javier-mileis-transition-team%2Farticleshow%2F105657787.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105657787.cms%5C%22