20These%20reports%20have%20details%20of%20all%20donations%20of%20Rs%2020%2C000%20and%20above%20through%20cheques%2C%20bank%20transfers%2C%20online%20transactions%20and%20UPI%20payments.%20The%20%3C%2Fspan%3Edonations%20are%20received%20from%20individuals%2C%20electoral%20trusts%2C%20companies%20and%20associations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20law%2C%20political%20parties%20need%20to%20submit%20details%20of%20all%20donations%20received%20by%20them%2C%20above%20Rs%2020%2C000%20and%20details%20of%20donors%20such%20as%20names%2C%20PAN%20card%20numbers%20and%20addresses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reports%20do%20not%20include%20donations%20that%20parties%20have%20received%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20which%20make%20the%20identities%20of%20donors%20completely%20secret.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fbjp-got-rs-719-cr-in-donations-last-yr-minus-poll-bonds-9049406%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Cspan%3E%20the%20BJP%20received%20about%2035%25%20of%20the%20donations%20in%202022-23%20from%20the%20Prudent%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20which%20gave%20the%20BJP%20Rs%20256.25%20crore%20in%20total.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Einzigartig%20Electoral%20Trust%20and%20Triumph%20Electoral%20Trust%20have%20Rs%208%20lakh%20and%20Rs%2010%20lakh%2C%20respectively%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EElectoral%20trusts%20are%20non-profit%20organisations%20which%20are%20set%20up%20by%20companies%20with%20the%20sole%20objective%20of%20distributing%20contributions%20they%20receive%20to%20political%20parties.%20The%20contributions%20come%20largely%20come%20from%20corporate%20entities%20or%20business%20houses%20registered%20in%20India%2C%20although%20individuals%20are%20also%20allowed%20to%20make%20donations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20individual%20donors%20are%20chief%20ministers%20Himanta%20Biswa%20Sarma%20(Assam)%2C%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20(Uttar%20Pradesh)%20and%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%20(Madhya%20Pradesh).%20According%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20among%20the%20donors%20are%20also%20mining%20companies%2C%20construction%20firms%2C%20waste%20management%20companies%2C%20distilleries%20and%20restaurants.%20Also%20are%20small%20businesses%2C%20private%20schools%2C%20education%20and%20charitable%20trusts.%20Plant%20nurseries%2C%20wine%20shops%2C%20%E2%80%98atta%20chakkis%E2%80%99%20and%20hardware%20stores%20are%20among%20the%20small%20businesses%20on%20the%20donors%E2%80%99%20list.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EOther%20parties%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20contribution%20report%20of%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%2C%20also%20posted%20on%20the%20ECI%20website%20on%20Thursday%2C%20showed%20declared%20donations%20of%20Rs%206.02%20crore.%20The%20CPI%20(M)%20does%20not%20accept%20electoral%20bonds%20and%20is%20the%20only%20political%20party%20amongst%20the%20petitioners%20in%20court%20to%20contest%20their%20constitutionality.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAAP%20declared%20Rs%2037%20crore%20for%20FY%202022-23%20and%20the%20BSP%20declared%20zero%20donations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20can%20read%20the%20reports%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feci.gov.in%2Ffiles%2Fcategory%2F1646-recognized-national-parties%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EElectoral%20bonds%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20opacity%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20has%20been%20heard%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20verdict%20has%20been%20reserved.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EElectoral%20bonds%20generated%20donations%20worth%20over%20Rs%209%2C188%20crore%20for%20all%20political%20parties%20in%20the%20past%20six%20years%2C%20according%20to%20data%20released%20by%20the%20Association%20of%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20BJP%20got%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20securing%2057%25%20of%20the%20total%20donations%2C%20as%20per%20ADR.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20which%20can%20be%20purchased%20in%20denominations%20worth%20crores%20of%20rupees%2C%20recipient%20political%20parties%20are%20required%20to%20only%20cite%20the%20total%20amount%20received%20to%20the%20ECI%20in%20their%20annual%20audited%20statements.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20money%20that%20the%20BJP%20has%20received%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20is%20in%20excess%20of%20what%20it%20has%20received%20from%20other%20declared%20sources.%20In%202021-22%2C%20the%20BJP%20declared%20Rs%201%2C033.70%20crore%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20but%20only%20Rs%20614.52%20crore%20through%20other%20contributions.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20counsel%2C%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%2C%20raised%20eyebrows%20when%20he%20argued%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cprivacy%E2%80%9D%20of%20donors%20to%20political%20parties.%20There%20was%20considerable%20heat%20generated%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fcitizens-dont-have-right-to-information-regarding-funding-of-a-political-party-centre-tells-supreme-court-in-electoral-bonds-case-241137%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eattorney%20general%20for%20India%20R%20Venkataramani%E2%80%99s%20statement%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20during%20the%20course%20of%20the%20case%20that%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ecitizens%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20right%20to%20know%20the%20source%20of%20funds%20received%20by%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eraft%20of%20petitions%20have%20opposed%20the%20call%20for%20%E2%80%9Cprivacy%E2%80%9D%20and%20made%20the%20case%20for%20transparency%2C%20to%20know%20who%20is%20funding%20which%20party%20and%20where%20that%20money%20is%20coming%20from.%20The%20controversial%20scheme%2C%20which%20began%20in%202017%2C%20makes%20it%20possible%20for%20companies%20to%20be%20set%20up%20and%20donate%20all%20proceeds%20to%20political%20parties.%20Earlier%2C%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20profits%20could%20be%20donated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701426619000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01145249%2F406110211_773446158163006_4756603232278021214_n.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2F2022-23-bjp-rs-720-crore-donations-non-electoral-bond-sources%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20previous%20financial%20year%2C%20the%20BJP%20declared%20that%20it%20received%20Rs%20614.52%20crore%20through%20cheques%2C%20bank%20transfers%2C%20online%20transactions%20and%20UPI%20payments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2F2022-23-bjp-rs-720-crore-donations-non-electoral-bond-sources%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ukraine%20war%3A%20Zelensky%20says%20fortifying%20front%20lines%20must%20be%20accelerated%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701425648000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F3A01%2Fproduction%2F_131894841_6adfe195c614392a35b59302768279be708fb03e0_29_2500_14071000x563.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67587331%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ukraine's%20president%20meets%20frontline%20commanders%20and%20says%20winter%20is%20a%20new%20phase%20of%20the%20war%20with%20Russia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A61%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67587331%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67587331.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67587331.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Paraguay%20Replaces%20Govt%20Official%20Who%20Signed%20Deal%20With%20Fugitive%20Nithyananda's%20Fictional%20Country%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F11%2F19123011%2Fnithyananda.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20Paraguayan%20government%20official%20has%20been%20replaced%20after%20he%20mistakenly%20signed%20a%20deal%20with%20%E2%80%98Kailasa%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20the%20fictional%20country%20created%20by%20fugitive%20Indian%20godman%20Nithyananda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fkailasa-paraguay-india-hindu-chamorro-bec1acb8178cfe645392f0f1aae75a58%5C%22%3EAssociated%20Press%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Arnaldo%20Chamorro%20was%20replaced%20as%20chief%20of%20staff%20for%20Paraguay%E2%80%99s%20agriculture%20ministry%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20soon%20after%20it%20came%20to%20light%20that%20he%20had%20signed%20a%20%E2%80%9Cproclamation%E2%80%9D%20with%20representatives%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9CUnited%20States%20of%20Kailasa%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proclamation%20reportedly%20expressed%20the%20%E2%80%9Csincere%20wish%20and%20recommendation%20for%20the%20government%20of%20Paraguay%20to%20consider%2C%20explore%20and%20actively%20seek%20the%20establishment%20of%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20the%20United%20States%20of%20Kailasa%20and%20support%20the%20admission%20of%20the%20United%20States%20of%20Kailasa%20as%20a%20sovereign%20and%20independent%20state%20in%20various%20international%20organizations%2C%20including%2C%20among%20others%2C%20the%20United%20Nations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20Chamorro%2C%20%E2%80%98Kailasa%E2%80%99%20representatives%20had%20also%20met%20agriculture%20minister%20Carlos%20Gim%C3%A9nez.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20update%20was%20met%20with%20ridicule%20online%2C%20this%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20government%20authorities%20have%20been%20tricked%20into%20believing%20Kailasa%20is%20a%20real%20country.%20In%20March%20this%20year%2C%20it%20came%20to%20light%20that%20the%20city%20of%20Newark%20in%20the%20United%20States%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fcity-of-newark-accidentally-signed-agreement-with-fugitive-godman-nithyanandas-kailasa%5C%22%3Esigned%20a%20sister-city%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Kailasa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20representatives%20of%20the%20so-called%20country%20also%20attended%20an%20event%20organised%20by%20a%20UN%20committee%20in%20Geneva%20on%20February%2024.%20One%20of%20them%20even%20spoke%20at%20the%20event.%20Vijayapriya%20Nithyananda%2C%20who%20has%20a%20tattoo%20of%20the%20godman%20on%20her%20arm%2C%20claimed%20that%20Kailasa%20has%20been%20implementing%20%E2%80%9Cancient%20Hindu%20policies%20and%20indigenous%20solutions%E2%80%9D%20for%20sustainable%20development%20in%20her%20so-called%20country.%20She%20also%20said%20that%20Nithyananda%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Cpersecuted%20by%20anti-Hindu%20elements%E2%80%9D%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETamil%20Nadu-native%20Nithyananda%2C%20whose%20real%20name%20is%20Rajashekharan%2C%20allegedly%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fgujarat-godman-nithyananda-booked-two-disciples-held-for-kidnapping%5C%22%3Efled%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0India%20in%202019%20after%20security%20agencies%20began%20probing%20his%20involvement%20in%20criminal%20cases%20including%20a%20rape%20case%20in%20Karnataka.%20The%20case%20pertained%20to%20two%20girls%20who%20went%20missing%20from%20his%20ashram.%20His%20passport%20expired%20in%20September%202018%20and%20police%20have%20since%20declined%20his%20requests%20for%20a%20renewal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202018%2C%20Gujarat%20Police%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%